						<summary>

						<p>On the north base of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Madhyasthanāthēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅga III. Year 11: 1198-1199 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of a gong (<hi rend="italic">śekaṇḍi</hi>), weighing 52 <hi rend="italic">palams</hi> by Kaḷattūruḍaiyāṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Periyaṉāḷi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Tiruchchiṟṟambala-vēḷān to god Tirunāgīśu[ra*]muḍaiyār.</p>						

